# {{.Name}} — AI Agent Context

## Goal
Minimal TypeScript program (Node 20+) that connects to ClutchCall over WebTransport and places an outbound call.

## Runtime
- Endpoint: `{{.Endpoint}}` (override via `CLUTCHCALL_ENDPOINT`)
- Auth: pre-signed JWT via `CLUTCHCALL_JWT` (service-account JWT minted by your backend).
- The SDK ships an Emscripten-compiled WASM core. Do not import the native FFI from Node;
  use `@clutchcall/sdk` which loads the WASM module for you.

## Editing Rules
- Audio buffers must be exchanged as `Uint8Array`, never `string`. Emscripten's UTF-8
  decoder corrupts byte values ≥ 0x80 (audio frames in PCMU/PCMA range).
- Use `typed_memory_view` exports from the WASM core to read frames. Never round-trip
  audio through `JSON.stringify`.
- Do not hand-edit any types in `node_modules/@clutchcall/sdk/dist/serde`. They are
  regenerated upstream by `apirpc_compiler`.

## Common Tasks
- Browser variant: see `clutchcall-sdk/typescript/examples/browser_demo.ts`.
- LLM bridge: see `clutchcall-sdk/typescript/examples/openai_realtime_demux.ts`.
